# QA Tools and Actions

## New LLM action

1. Add type + Zod schema in @src/domain/schemas/action.schema.ts
2. Implement handler in `src/application/tools/built-in/` (or extend registry)
3. Update `ActionPolicyService` if destructive or policy-sensitive
4. Update LLM provider prompts if the action is user-facing
5. Add Vitest coverage in `test/`

## New QA tool

1. Create `src/application/tools/built-in/<name>.tool.ts` implementing `QaTool` (`execute`)
2. Export in @src/application/tools/built-in/index.ts
3. `QaToolRegistry` loads via `ALL_QA_TOOLS` in `ApplicationModule`
4. Distinguish public vs internal tools (@src/application/tools/built-in/public-tools.ts)

## Validation

Never trust raw LLM output — always `safeParse` with `QaActionEnvelopeSchema` and respect `llm.maxSchemaRetries`.

## Execution modes

Respect `runtime.mode`: `FULL_REACTIVE` vs Hybrid Guarded (`HYBRID_GUARDED`, `PLAN_AND_EXECUTE`). See @doc/release-notes/v0.2-stable.md.
